Loops:

- while loop
  define and initialize a variable
  while(condition)
  {
    if condition is true, code here will execute, else not execute
    I/D;
  }


- for loop


  for(define and initialize a variable;condition;I/D)
  {
    if condition is true, code here will execute, else not execute
  }


- advanced for loop [for each loop]


We should mostly use for loop we know the exact starting & end points

if we are not sure of end point, only while preferred OR

when we are not sure about the number of iterations, we prefer while loop

